Bits Field Name Description Type Reset
31:1 DWT Points to the Data Watchpoint and Trace block at 0xE0001000.
(2*DWT + Base address for ROM_TABLE) & 0x0FFFFFFF0 = 0xE0001000.		 RO 0b111 1111 1111 1000 0001 0000 0000 0001
0 DWT_PRESENT 0: DWT is not present
1: DWT is present.		 RO 1

TOP:CPU_ROM_TABLE:END

Address Offset 0x0000 0018
Physical Address 0xE00F F018 Instance 0xE00F F018
Description End Marker
Marks the end of the ROM table. If CoreSight components are added, they are added starting from this location and the End marker is moved to the next location after the additional components.
Type RO
Bits Field Name Description Type Reset
31:0 END End of the ROM table RO 0x0000 0000

Address Offset 0x0000 0FCC
Physical Address 0xE00F FFCC Instance 0xE00F FFCC
Description System Memory Map Access for DAP
Type RO
Bits Field Name Description Type Reset
31:1 RESERVED1 Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior. RO 0b000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0 SYSTEM_ACCESS 1: The system memory map is accessible using the DAP
0: Only debug resources are accessible using the DAP		 RO 1
